# Pending Work & Known Issues

## Ready to Build

- **Junior Framers 2026 roster/schedule**: Populate when USTA data is available
- **Doubles World Championships (post-summer, blocked on signups)**: Aspirational follow-up to the singles championship. Brainstormed direction: rotating weekly auto-balanced pairings (not fixed pairs), individual standings. NOTE: the existing `tournament_participants.partner_id` column is the **wrong shape** for this — partner needs to live on the match, not the participant. Don't start until signups exist and player count is known (format depends on N). Do NOT just render `partner_name` on the singles page as "doubles UI" — that ships a half-built fixed-pair model.
- **League opponent lineup prediction**: Use TennisRecord scouting data to predict likely opponent lineups
- **Payment dashboard polish**: Show pot calculations, refund tracking for no-show buffer
- **Web Push notifications**: Deferred in favor of email, but infrastructure exists

## Tried and Abandoned (don't re-attempt)

- **Venmo payment auto-recording (via email)**: Was going to route `venmo@framers.app` inbound through `framers-email-router` to parse Venmo notification emails and auto-write to `payments`. Abandoned because **Venmo does not actually send any real-time signal when money is deposited into a business/business-profile account** — no notification email, no webhook, nothing. The trigger we needed doesn't exist. Stick with the manual flow: a "Pay via Venmo" link to `account.venmo.com/u/bjori` and admins manually record receipts in `/admin/payments`. If you ever want to revisit, the only viable paths are Venmo's official Business API (paid + approval-gated) or screen-scraping the account history (terms-of-service risk).

