## Known Issues

- **ICS feed**: Works well but some calendar clients may cache aggressively (max-age=0 is set)
- **USTA sync**: Regex-based HTML scraping — fragile if USTA changes their markup
- **TennisRecord scraping**: Also regex-based — fragile if tennisrecord.com changes markup
- **Dark mode contrast**: Was fixed systemically but may regress if new hardcoded colors are added
- **Local network**: Zscaler/WiFi blocks tennisrecord.com and some workers.dev URLs from dev machine
- **`reliability_score` is per-player but should be per-`team_memberships`**: A player on multiple active teams (e.g., Hannes/Matt once Junior Framers 2026 is active alongside Senior Framers 2026) gets a single shared `players.reliability_score` that's overwritten by whichever team's `updateReliabilityScores` runs last in the cron loop. Mitigated for now by `ORDER BY id` on the cron's `ustaTeams` SELECT (deterministic but still wrong — players see the score for an arbitrary team). Real fix: move the column to `team_memberships(team_id, player_id, reliability_score)`, update `carrot.ts` writers, update the lineup-optimizer's `AvailablePlayer.reliabilityScore` source. ~1-2 hours of work; do it before Junior Framers 2026 starts playing matches.

## Architecture Notes

- The old tournament site `greenbrook-champs.pages.dev` now redirects to `framers.app`. Its KV data is preserved but not actively used
- `src/app/api/debug/route.ts` has admin actions — protected by `ADMIN_SECRET` (Bearer, X-Admin-Secret, or ?key=)
- Unauthenticated `setup` also requires `ADMIN_SECRET`
- `src/app/api/setup/route.ts` is the schema source of truth — update it when adding tables/columns
- Scores in tournament_matches use JSON arrays (`"[6,4,10]"`) — always parse with `JSON.parse()` in a try/catch
- The `app_events` table serves double duty: analytics dashboard AND cron deduplication
- AI form/quip generation is fire-and-forget — don't block user responses on GPT calls
- TennisRecord data has a 7-day staleness window — only re-fetched when stale
